Spatial particle filter: A method for tracking multi-targets from 4D live cell imaging data.

COMPILATION:

1. Get all the source codes registered in this repositry and move them to the current directory.

2. Type 'make'. Then you get the binary file 'track' for tracking multi-objects.


INPUT DATA FORMAT:

The format of input 4D image should be encoded in the following binary format:  
  
I: The number of voxels along x axis (int: 4 bytes)  
J: The number of voxels along y axis (int: 4 bytes)  
K: The number of voxels along z axis (int: 4 bytes)  
T: The number of frames (int: 4 bytes)  
s: The signal intensity of voxel (i,j,k)=(  0,  0,  0) at time t=0 (usigned char: 1 byte)  
s: The signal intensity of voxel (i,j,k)=(  1,  0,  0) at time t=0 (usigned char: 1 byte)  
...  
s: The signal intensity of voxel (i,j,k)=(I-1,  0,  0) at time t=0 (usigned char: 1 byte)  
s: The signal intensity of voxel (i,j,k)=(  0,  1,  0) at time t=0 (usigned char: 1 byte)  
...  
s: The signal intensity of voxel (i,j,k)=(I-1,J-1,  0) at time t=0 (usigned char: 1 byte)  
...  
s: The signal intensity of voxel (i,j,k)=(I-1,J-1,K-1) at time t=0 (usigned char: 1 byte)  
s: The signal intensity of voxel (i,j,k)=(  0,  0,  0) at time t=1 (usigned char: 1 byte)  
...  
s: The signal intensity of voxel (i,j,k)=(I-1,J-1,K-1) at time t=T-1 (usigned char: 1 byte)  

** NOTE:  
** Signal values MUST range from 0 to 255.    
** Separators such as '\t' and '\n' must NOT be inserted.  


USAGE:

In the current directory, type the folloing command:  

./track input-file-name

If the tracking is finished, the output file 'result.bin' is output.
Then, type the following command:  

./view input-file-name result.bin  

Currently, this viewer is for Mac only ('Xquartz' MUST be installed beforehand). 
A sample input file 'sample4D.bin' is available at 
https://sites.google.com/site/webosamuhirose/home/data


